{"id": "general-chat--general--covert-node-installs", "title": "Covert Node Installs", "forum": "General Chat", "messages": [{"id": "1438823090204184700", "author": "PoorSignal", "author_handle": "psidnell", "user_id": "828549897393143808", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/828549897393143808/12a1f0928739bd89d020469c18eea904.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, November 14, 2025 4:29 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-11-14 4:29 a.m.", "text": "I found this old tree in a copse at the top of a hill. It's just a heltec in a ziploc bag held on with bungees while I wait for nRF solar kit. The branches start 30/40 ft up and the ivy disguises the straps. The trunk gets sun (when there is sun in the UK) in the afternoon. Hoping that'll be enough. It's a long walk with a telescopic ladder but it's about 12ft up, out of easy reach of kids/cows. Will post pics of the final install when done - probably next week. I was looking for a way to attach without damaging the tree and plan to use a ratchet strap with green webbing. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I found this old tree in a copse at the top of a hill. It&#39;s just a heltec in a ziploc bag held on with bungees while I wait for nRF solar kit. The branches start 30/40 ft up and the ivy disguises the straps. The trunk gets sun (when there is sun in the UK) in the afternoon. Hoping that&#39;ll be enough. It&#39;s a long walk with a telescopic ladder but it&#39;s about 12ft up, out of easy reach of kids/cows. Will post pics of the final install when done - probably next week. I was looking for a way to attach without damaging the tree and plan to use a ratchet strap with green webbing.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Friday, November 14, 2025 5:06 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1438824917943582791", "author": "PoorSignal", "author_handle": "psidnell", "user_id": "828549897393143808", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/828549897393143808/12a1f0928739bd89d020469c18eea904.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, November 14, 2025 4:36 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-11-14 4:36 a.m.", "text": "View not bad, can see Dundry, Bristol & South Wales. I had to go up yesterday to change the battery and had trouble finding it - which I guess is a good thing. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>View not bad, can see Dundry, Bristol &amp; South Wales. I had to go up yesterday to change the battery and had trouble finding it - which I guess is a good thing.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Friday, November 14, 2025 5:11 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1438833352936525966", "author": "PoorSignal", "author_handle": "psidnell", "user_id": "828549897393143808", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/828549897393143808/12a1f0928739bd89d020469c18eea904.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, November 14, 2025 5:10 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-11-14 5:10 a.m.", "text": "", "content_html": "", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/14